slick-object-pool provides CMake targets:

    find_package(slick_object_pool CONFIG REQUIRED)
    target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE slick_object_pool)

The package is header-only. Simply include the header in your code:

    #include <slick/object_pool.h>

Example usage:

    slick::ObjectPool<MyStruct> pool(1024);  // Power of 2
    auto* obj = pool.allocate();
    obj->field = value;
    pool.free(obj);
